To change the background color of your Android app to white, you can do it in a few different ways. 

Firstly, if you want to set the background color statically, you can add `android:background="#FFFFFF"` to your layout file (e.g., `/res/layout/activity_main.xml`). This will set the background color to white.

If you want to change the background dynamically, you'll need to use some code. You can do this by finding a View in your activity and calling `view.setBackgroundColor(Color.WHITE)` on it. For example:

```java
public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {
    @Override
