// ... set properties ...
session.merge(user);
```
Alternatively, you can use `session.saveOrUpdate()`, which will check if the object is already in the session and either save or update it accordingly.

Another approach is to make sure that your objects are properly detached from the session before trying to save them. You can do this by calling `session.evict()` on the object:
```java
User user = new User();
// ... set properties ...
session.save(user);
session.evict(user); // Detach the object from the session
```
Finally, if you're using a primary key generator that generates IDs with values like 0 (which can indicate an ID not yet set), you might need to handle those cases separately.

